### Description

The bug with hash/range partitioning schemes is a bit different from #10012. With hash/range partitioning, the task sets some size of the core partitions, but it could be wrong. More precisely, there can be some empty partitions in the core partitions. If that's the case, those segments will never become online on brokers. This can happen because the batch ingestion task allocates all partitionIds upfront before it starts ingestion. However, if your data is highly skewed, some hash/range buckets can be empty even after the task consumed all inputs. Since Druid doesn't create empty partitions, those empty buckets will be missing in the core partitions which make the other segments to never become online.

This PR fixes this issue by postponing the partitionId allocation until all empty buckets are identified. To do so, the partitionId and bucketId are now decoupled. The shardSpec for hash partitioning is:

```java
  @JsonCreator
  public HashBasedNumberedShardSpec(
      @JsonProperty("partitionNum") int partitionNum,    // partitionId
      @JsonProperty("partitions") int partitions,        // core partition set size
      @JsonProperty("bucketId") @Nullable Integer bucketId, // nullable for backward compatibility
      @JsonProperty("numBuckets") @Nullable Integer numBuckets, // nullable for backward compatibility
      @JsonProperty("partitionDimensions") @Nullable List<String> partitionDimensions,
      @JacksonInject ObjectMapper jsonMapper
  )
  {
    super(partitionNum, partitions);
    // Use partitionId as bucketId if it's missing.
    this.bucketId = bucketId == null ? partitionNum : bucketId;
    // If numBuckets is missing, assume that any hash bucket is not empty.
    // Use the core partition set size as the number of buckets.
    this.numBuckets = numBuckets == null ? partitions : numBuckets;
    this.jsonMapper = jsonMapper;
    this.partitionDimensions = partitionDimensions == null ? DEFAULT_PARTITION_DIMENSIONS : partitionDimensions;
  }
```

The bucketId is allocated upfront when all buckets are created, but the partitionId is dynamically allocated when a bucket is actually in use. To implement this, a new interface (`BucketNumberedShardSpec`) and its implementations were added. 

`BuildingHashBasedNumberedShardSpec` was also added to address the same issue in #10012 for hash partitioning. Finally, two fields of `bucketId` and `numBuckets` were added in `HashBasedNumberedShardSpec` to decouple the core partitions and the hash buckets.

The same technique was implemented for the range partitioning as well. This is because 1) the range partitioning has the same issue and 2) it's harder to fix only hash partitioning part. As a result, a new field `numCorePartitions` was added in `SingleDimensionShardSpec` which is initialized to -1 if it's missing. 

```java
  @JsonCreator
  public SingleDimensionShardSpec(
      @JsonProperty("dimension") String dimension,
      @JsonProperty("start") @Nullable String start,
      @JsonProperty("end") @Nullable String end,
      @JsonProperty("partitionNum") int partitionNum,
      @JsonProperty("numCorePartitions") @Nullable Integer numCorePartitions // nullable for backward compatibility
  )
  {
    Preconditions.checkArgument(partitionNum >= 0, "partitionNum >= 0");
    this.dimension = Preconditions.checkNotNull(dimension, "dimension");
    this.start = start;
    this.end = end;
    this.partitionNum = partitionNum;
    this.numCorePartitions = numCorePartitions == null ? UNKNOWN_NUM_CORE_PARTITIONS : numCorePartitions;
  }
```

Also, now `SingleDimensionShardSpec` uses the same mechanism with `HashBasedNumberedShardSpec` to check the completeness of the core partition set, it creates `NumberedPartitionChunk` in `createChunk()`.

The changes in `HashBasedNumberedShardSpec` and `SingleDimensionShardSpec` should be compatible with older versions; Druid still can read segments created in older versions. The segments created with the new field is still readable in older versions of druid. However, those segments might not become online after downgrade if there are empty buckets in the core partitions.

